The paper deals with the problem of few-shot fine-grained recognition in images, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed model involves feature fusion and high-order integration, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a dataset related to marine ecological environment, which could fall under the subfield of computational biology (cs.CL) or information retrieval (cs.IR) for image-based search and classification.
